            </div>
          </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="no-margins" />

  <section class="xrt-section">
    <div class="layout">

      <h2 class="m-t-0">{$tr("Utility of the Robonomics Token ($XRT) in Polkadot")}</h2>

      <h3 class="title-lined"><span>{$tr("What XRT Enables")}</span></h3>
      <p>
        {$tr("XRT allows users to purchase monthly Web3 cloud subscriptions with predictable latency‚Äîessential for IoT use cases‚Äîwhich directly fuel its deflationary model. Users can also pay per transaction.")}
      </p>

      <div class="oldy space-b">
        <p>
          <b>{$tr('Collators')}</b> {$tr('(who produce blocks) receive small incentives. The Robonomics Rollup now pays monthly for shared security‚Äîa shift from the previous annual or biannual model. To cover these costs, the protocol mints new tokens.')}
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>
        {$tr('The combination of protocol-level token issuance and real user demand from IoT subscriptions creates a dynamic, developer-independent market for XRT. This market is crucial for building a globally accessible, decentralized cloud‚Äîone that could support every smart home, wearable, or personal robot ü§ñ.')}
      </p>

     
      <p>
        {$tr('When user activity and subscriptions increase while infrastructure costs remain low')} ‚Üí <b>{$tr('deflation')}</b>.  
        {$tr('When usage drops and costs rise')} ‚Üí <b>{$tr('inflation')}</b>.  
        {$tr('This mechanism maintains a stable and economically balanced system.')}
      </p>

      <p>
        {$tr('This is also why Robonomics doesn‚Äôt use staking‚Äîcybersecurity is handled by Polkadot validators, who are paid directly.')}
      </p>

       <h3 class="title-lined"><span>{$tr("XRT Token Lifecycle in Robonomics")}</span></h3>

      <figure class="xrt-image">
        <img src="/images/xrt/xrt-scheme.webp" alt="Robonomics token lifecycle scheme" />
        <figcaption>{$tr('Robonomics #parachain token lifecycle in Kusama network')}</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h3 class="title-lined"><span>{$tr("Transaction Logic & Subscription Model")}</span></h3>
      

      <ul class="space-b-2">
        <li>{$tr('XRT can be used to pay one-time fees for transactions (launch, liability, datalog, digitalTwins).')}</li>
        <li>{$tr('Fees are split 50/50 between the parachain treasury and the block-producing collator.')}</li>
        <li>{$tr('Users can activate subscriptions, granting priority transaction processing over one-time payers.')}</li>
        <li>{$tr('Subscriptions are ideal for users needing predictable latency close to one block period.')}</li>
        <li>{$tr('Subscription fees are set via an ultra-fast auction (~10 blocks or ~1‚Äì2 minutes).')}</li>
        <li>{$tr('Winning subscription fees are burned, reducing total supply.')}</li>
      </ul>

       <h4 class="title-lined"><span>{$tr("Balanced Tokenomics")}</span></h4>
      <p>{$tr('Robonomics maintains balance through:')}</p>
      <ul class="space-t-05">
        <li><b>{$tr('Inflation')}</b> {$tr('occurs if lease costs exceed demand.')}</li>
        <li><b>{$tr('Deflation')}</b> {$tr('happens when subscription usage outweighs lease costs.')}</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

